name: What is Cinco de Mayo
summary: Cinco de Mayo, the Mexican-American holiday celebrated on May 5th, is often misunderstood. Contrary to popular belief, it does not commemorate Mexico's Independence Day, which falls on September 16th. Instead, it celebrates the Mexican victory over French forces at the Battle of Puebla on May 5th, 1862. While it is a significant event in Mexican-American culture, it holds lesser importance in Mexico itself.

name: Randy Travis
summary: With the aid of artificial intelligence (AI), Randy Travis has regained his singing voice and released his first song, 'Where That Came from,' since suffering a stroke in 2013. This groundbreaking collaboration involved the use of AI technology to analyze and synthesize Travis's pre-stroke vocal recordings, enabling him to sing again despite his impaired vocal cords. The new song has sparked both praise and discussion, raising questions about the role of AI in preserving and enhancing artistic expression.
